        "date":  "2026-07-16",
        "theme":  "Enterprise",
        "summary":  "Tech hiring is rebounding with unemployment at 3.1%, and IT leaders are investing heavily in internal training programs to address AI skill gaps. According to CompTIA research, 83% of IT leaders prioritize skill concerns, with 62% expecting increased AI training budgets. Organizations recognize that embedding AI into workflows and pairing employees with experienced colleagues is critical to closing the gap between training completion and actual job application.",
        "execSummary":  "Enterprise AI deployment is stalling not on technology but on talent: 83% of IT leaders flag skill gaps as a top concern, and 62% plan to increase AI training budgets. The critical implication is that tool rollout without workforce readiness produces poor adoption and wasted spend. Leaders should budget for structured AI upskilling programs ΓÇö including experiential, peer-pairing models ΓÇö not just licensing. The gap between completing training and confidently applying skills on the job is the metric to watch.",
