        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "CIOs face pressure to accelerate AI adoption while managing risks through proper governance and oversight. Industry leaders discuss strategies for balancing innovation speed with compliance, including organizational design approaches that create healthy internal tensions between AI adoption and risk management teams. Success requires building secure foundations that enable experimentation rather than impeding it.",
        "execSummary":  "The central tension for enterprise CIOs is no longer whether to adopt AI but how fast to move without outpacing governance capacity. The article surfaces an organizational design lever: deliberately structuring internal tensions between AI adoption advocates and risk/compliance teams to force productive tradeoffs. The key implication for leaders is that oversight structures must be designed to enable velocity, not just constrain it. CIOs who treat governance as a blocker rather than a strategic foundation will face compounding remediation costs downstream.",
